By Player



Distribution by Player


How does the grade distribution per player look like? I think thats one of the first questions that came to my mind.

From this, you can kind of get an idea how each player fared. Its also interesting to see how the distribution shapes differ between players. For example, some players received much more partial grades than others.Was it because more thought was put into them?

Its also intersting how some players tended to receive a default grade. (Donskoi was given a D grade much more frequent than his other grades.)

I think this graphic - combined with the next graphic - tell more about the nature of player grades than anything else.



GPA by Player


Distributions are great. But its easier to see the overall grade of a player when mapped to a GPA

This is one of my favorite graphics.

A few players didnt play as many games (Hutchinson, Kaut), so keep that in mind.

But this graphic is very interesting. Why is Calvert so high? Why is Compher so low?
